<br>
Sorry Calio, I like ya, but I'm calling bullshit on this statement...<br>
<br>
Abuse and being spanked are in two totally different areas...<br>
<br>
I grew up in the south... I got my fair share of spankings growing up, I wasn't abused for doing wrong, I got what I deserved punishment wise from my mother when I did wrong...<br>
<br>
But ultimately, I feel that children go wrong due to examples in their life...<br>
<br>
If a parent lives a deviant life, and doesn't instill quality morals in a child at a young age, that child grows up seeing what the parent does and tends to follow the example...<br>
<br>
Good example of this..<br>
<br>
Child lives with mother... Mother tries to tell child to live right way, etc... etc... but mother does deviant things in her life... child realises that mother does these things, then it must be okay for me to do them as well...<br>
<br>
I got my fair share of corporal punishment for the things I did wrong, and I honestly think it helped my character... if I would have had no discipline, no telling what I would have ended up doing...<br>
<br>
Sexual deviant parents, drug abuses, alcoholics, etc... all that kind of stuff in a childs life is an example, be it, a bad example, but the fact of the matter is, children tend to become a combination of their enviornment and the examples set before them...<br>
<br>
And before you anti child spanking people jump on the &quot;Well, if you spank your child, it will cause them to be abusive when they get older due to example&quot; thing...<br>
<br>
Yes, I think that ABUSE, can spawn ABUSE, but when you use corporal punishment to enforce rules, I don't think it hurts them mentally or physically in the long run...<br>
<br>
..Monkey see, money do...<br>
