It intrigues me that so many people seem to believe that &quot;discipline&quot;, &quot;consequences&quot; and, &quot;being put back in my place&quot; all involve hitting kids.  In other words, parents that enforce boundaries do so by hitting, and parents who do not hit, do not enforce boundaries.<br>
<br>
Rest assured that this is most definitely not the case.  Parents who do not hit their kids can nevertheless raise a disciplined and respectful child.  Interestingly enough, parents who do not hit their kids can ALSO be abusive and harmful to their child's well-being.<br>
<br>
It is not a simple on or off issue.  Children have a tremendous ability to place experiences into different contexts.  Not every pain is trauma, not every angry parental reaction is abuse.  But some are... it's the parent's responsibility -- alas, often badly managed -- to find the line between consequence and damage, between retribution and vengeance.<br>
<br>
Personally, I've never hit a child, mine or anybody else's.  I view that kind of punishment as dreadfully inefficient, irrelevant and fraught with a kind of risk that I dare not touch.  <br>
<br>
Moreover, it brings an inconsistent message to my child.  I do not control or affect my wife or my employees or my neighbors by hitting them when they are bad.  I do not resolve my problems with the long distance phone company by driving to their office and smacking them around.  I do not settle arguments with a fist, and even when it's Angry Bar Guy taking a shot at me, I study ways to handle those situations that don't involve a contest to see who can hit the hardest.<br>
<br>
Yet... I should hit my child when he is bad?  I can resolve all other issues in my life without hitting...except that one?  Nonsense.<br>
<br>
PoRrraowl <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eqkaneerfv>EQKaneerFV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.circleofsisters.net/vader.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Porn Knight</span><br>  Posts: 332<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/11/03 9:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3824.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.circleofsisters.net/vader.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Idiots in chat rooms, This is just plain bull.. sh... </span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Moreover, it brings an inconsistent message to my child. I do not control or affect my wife or my employees or my neighbors by hitting them when they are bad. I do not resolve my problems with the long distance phone company by driving to their office and smacking them around. I do not settle arguments with a fist, and even when it's Angry Bar Guy taking a shot at me, I study ways to handle those situations that don't involve a contest to see who can hit the hardest.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
