<br>
There is the fear while riding on the roller coaster, the fear of a really well done horror flick. Most of us would consider these good fears.<br>
<br>
There is the pain of exerting yourself that last bit more to win, the pain/pleasure of an intense orgasm, the stinging pain when the bat hits that ball just perfect. Again most of us would consider these good pains.<br>
<br>
Pleasure, pain, joy, hunger, tickles and fear are all sensations we experience and learn from as we grow as children. Pain and fear are two very important ones, they develop our survival instinct and teach us important lessons like fire is pretty but it bites.<br>
<br>
I would not wish any one experience intense pain and most definitely do not think abuse is a good lesson.<br>
<br>
I do think that children should experience small portions of the bad things in life as part of growing up to learn methods of living through it and moving past it. As a parent sometimes we need to let them try, sometimes feel the failure, be there to reassure them so they will move past their fear and pain and try again. I would be very concerned about a person that was overprotected as a child. Some may be shocked and end up hating life because they have not develop the personal tools of handling it others may just not feel like there are any consequences and lack some basic self preservation instincts. <br>
<br>
Just some of my random thoughts on life, childhood and raising children.<br>
